    "text": "**Winners: Virtuals Protocol, Bittensor, x402/pay‑rails, and standards (ERC‑8004 / UCP).** These projects dominate because they capture the three durable primitives for an agent economy: **payments**, **discovery/identity**, and **verifiable compute**.\n\n![AI Agents On-Chain Activity and Revenue](https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjriemfd/image/upload/v1746973912/veldt/ltahrqvmwfy85mxezqli.jpg)\n\n## Winners (what’s gaining traction)\n- **Virtuals Protocol** — **ACP/Butler** is the production commerce layer: **$300M+ aGDP** milestones, **$75M in protocol fees** this year, and **~1M registered agents**. Virtuals bundles agent launch, discovery, micropayments, and distribution into one stack.\n- **Bittensor (TAO)** — the decentralized intelligence backbone. The **TAO halving** (7,200 → 3,600 daily emissions) and institutional filings (Grayscale S‑1) accelerated onchain demand for model-provisioning infrastructure.\n- **x402 / PayAI / facilitator stack** — HTTP-native micropay rails enabling sub‑dollar pay‑per‑call. Network activity: **>2M daily x402 tx** and **$50–60M volume (30d)**; PayAI reports **28M tx / $7M settled** to date as a facilitator.\n- **Standards & discovery** — **ERC‑8004** (agent identity + reputation) and **UCP** (Universal Commerce Protocol) remove the brittle, manual glue that blocked agent-to-agent commerce.\n\n![Total aGDP Chart](https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjriemfd/image/upload/v1763741160/veldt/ekdj86sgcstlbhumyppw.jpg)\n\n## Why they win — core drivers\n- **Monetization-first rails.** Protocols that capture settlement (x402, Virtuals’ ACP) convert agent activity into recurring fees and measurable aGDP. **Fees > revenue** is the new moat, not TVL.\n- **Discovery + reputation.** With millions of agents, discoverability is the bottleneck. ERC‑8004 + marketplaces (MCP/Questflow) enable durable matching and reduce fraud risk.\n- **Verifiability & auditability.** Confidential/verifiable inference (TEEs, FHE attestations) lets agents deliver