ing custodial maturation and public market interest.  \n- **ZKsync** published a 2026 roadmap prioritizing institutional features (zkVM, privacy/standards).  \n- **Polygon Labs** completed a strategic acquisition (~**$250M+**) to push payments/stablecoin tooling.  \n- **Tether** froze roughly **$182M USDT** across addresses after law‑enforcement requests — compliance and custodial controls remain active market drivers.  \n- Privacy and reputation primitives are proliferating: confidential payments launched on **Base**, and onchain reputation models (neural net FairScore) are in early integrations.\n\nFocus: rails + revenue. Capital is moving toward chains and products that solve settlement, custody, privacy, and institutional execution. Agentic AI and prediction markets are new demand centers; memecoin episodes remain the primary operational downside risk.",
